***Task 1.1***
Load the following sentences into a RDD: `Spark I am your father`, `May the Spark be with you`, `May Spark live long and prosper`. Split the sentences into words. Use `map` and `flatMap`. What is the difference?

***Task 1.2***
Count the number of occurences of each word over all sentences using a RDD.

***Task 3.2***
In case of wrong inferred data types correct them manually and load the file again with corrected data types.

msg.data:
Task 3.2
In case of wrong inferred data types correct them manually and load the file again with corrected data types.
import org.apache.spark.sql.types.{StructType, StructField, StringType, IntegerType, TimestampType, DoubleType}

paragraphs.text:
%md
### Solution 3.2

msg.data: Solution 3.2

paragraphs.text:
%spark
import org.apache.spark.sql.types.{StructType,StructField,StringType,IntegerType,TimestampType,DoubleType}

// Manually define the schema
val taxiSchema = StructType(List(StructField("medallion", StringType),
                                 StructField("rate_code", IntegerType),
                                 StructField("pickup_datetime", TimestampType),
                                 StructField("trip_distance", DoubleType),
                                 StructField("store_and_fwd_flag", StringType)))

val taxiSnapshot = spark.read.option("header", true)
                             .option("delimiter", " ")
                             .option("timestampFormat", "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSSZ")
                             .schema(taxiSchema)
                             .csv("s3a://cs-spark-basic-training/exercises/chapter3/")

taxiSnapshot.printSchema()

taxiSnapshot.show(50, false)

### Solution 5.3.1

msg.data: Solution 5.3.1

paragraphs.text:
%spark
//Construct all non-primes from 2 to 500 k (duplicates are tolerated)
val nonPrimes = sc.parallelize(2 to 500000)
                  .map(x => (x, (2 to (500000 / x))))
println("nonPrimes is distributed across " + nonPrimes.getNumPartitions.toString + " partitions")

val nonPrimesFlat = nonPrimes.flatMap(kv => kv._2.map(_ * kv._1))
println("nonPrimesFlat is distributed across " + nonPrimesFlat.getNumPartitions.toString + " partitions")

//Get all primes by excluding all non-primes from 2 to 500 k
val prime = sc.parallelize(2 to 500000).subtract(nonPrimesFlat)
println("prime is distributed across " + prime.getNumPartitions.toString + " partitions")

//Display 10 primes
println("*************** RESULT ***************")
prime.take(10).foreach(println)

### Solution 5.3.2

msg.data: Solution 5.3.2

paragraphs.text:
%spark
//Construct all non-primes from 2 to 500 k (duplicates are tolerated)
val nonPrimes = sc.parallelize(2 to 500000)
                  .map(x => (x, (2 to (500000 / x))))
println(nonPrimes.getNumPartitions)                  

//Rule of thumb: number of partitions = cores per CPU * CPU per cluster * 2 or 3
val nonPrimesRep = nonPrimes.repartition(36)
println(nonPrimesRep.getNumPartitions)

val nonPrimesRepFlat = nonPrimesRep.flatMap(kv => kv._2.map(_ * kv._1))                
println(nonPrimesRepFlat.getNumPartitions)

//Get all primes by excluding all non-primes from 2 to 500 k
val prime = sc.parallelize(2 to 500000).subtract(nonPrimesRepFlat)
println(prime.getNumPartitions)

//Dispaly 10 primes
prime.take(10).foreach(println)
